cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a nonparametric topic model for labeled data using a mixture of random measures as a base distribution of the Dirichlet process. It also compares its performance with other machine learning models such as MedLDA, LDA-SVM, and Labeled-LDA. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with modeling labeled data in the form of corpora of documents. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a novel approach to topic modeling. 

Computer vision (cs.CV) is another possible sub-category as the paper also applies the model to multi-labeled images for image segmentation and object labeling, comparing its performance with nCuts and rddCRP. 

Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as topic modeling is often used in analyzing social networks and information retrieval.
